[thinking] I think Falcon512 should work without issues, but I'm wondering if the native implementation will be slower, possibly taking under 60 seconds. Existing tests have used simpler, direct parameters. My approach suggests using KeyPairGenerator.getInstance("FALCON", provider) and initializing it with FalconParameterSpec.falcon_512 alongside a SecureRandom instance, maybe even a seeded one. While this could be nondeterministic, it should be fine. It may be better to use SecureRandom.getInstance("SHA1PRNG") and set the seed properly.
